Egypt won through to the Africa Cup of Nations final on Wednesday after beating Burkina Faso 4-3 on penalties in the semi-final.The match in Libreville ended 1-1 after 90 minutes and extra time, with Mohamed Salah&#8217;s 66th-minute opener for Egypt cancelled out by Aristide Bance seven minutes later.With no further scoring it went to a shoot-out where Essam El Hadary&#8217;s save from Bertrand Traore&#8217;s last kick for Burkina Faso gave Egypt the victory.They will play either Ghana or Cameroon in Sunday&#8217;s final.-AFP